proxmox-datacenter-manager (1.1.5) trixie; urgency=medium

  * fix #7639: remote task cache: when advancing the per-node poll cutoff,
    account for tasks that are still running, so a long-running task that
    overlaps a shorter, already-finished one is no longer skipped and lost from
    the task archive:
    - running tasks not started by the Datacenter Manager now also show up in
      the task views
    - poll known active tasks every 30 seconds instead of waiting up to ten
      minutes for the next regular poll, so a running task no longer appears
      stuck

  * remote guest consoles: connect to a guest's console directly from the
    Datacenter Manager. The API daemon now proxies both the noVNC graphical
    console and the xterm.js serial console of QEMU and LXC guests on Proxmox
    VE remotes, and serves the noVNC and xterm.js web assets:
    - pin the novnc-pve and pve-xtermjs dependencies to the versions that
      provide the index templates and serial-console URL handling the daemon
      relies on, so an older asset package cannot silently break console
      serving

  * remote connections: back off from unreachable remotes instead of retrying
    a connection on every request, so API calls to an offline remote return the
    last error immediately rather than stalling on a connection timeout each
    time:
    - resume probing in growing intervals and reset the back-off as soon as the
      host answers again
    - when no remote is reachable at all, assume the local network is at fault
      and keep probing a single remote without backing off, so all remotes
      recover promptly once connectivity returns
    - apply the same host cache and back-off handling to Proxmox Backup Server
      remotes

  * subscription: count each remote subscription only once toward the node
    total, so adding the same subscribed remote multiple times can no longer
    inflate the count.

  * node system log: stream the reader's output directly instead of buffering
    the whole journal, so large logs no longer load fully into memory.

